detail.title: Reduce Inflation - Phase 2
detail.description:
# Reduce Inflation Rate 

This proposal is the second phase of implementing the XKI v2 tokenomics voted by the community in [proposal #9](https://www.mintscan.io/ki-chain/proposals/9). This parameter-change proposal aims at reducing the inflation from 9% to 6.75% starting October 2nd (Phase 2).

By voting YES to this proposal the KiChain community agrees on reducing the inflation to 6.75%

detail.title: [COSC] Portfolio restructuring
detail.description:
# Summary:
This proposal seeks to rebalance the assets included in the Cosmos Core portfolio by swapping $JUNO, the Juno Network’s governance token, to the Akash Network token; $AKT.

# Motivation:
When we launched Cosmos Core, the $JUNO token represented over 20% of $COSC collateral. A percentage that has dwindled over the time due to $JUNO’s negative price action against other collateral assets backing $COSC. At the time of writing, $JUNO represents less than 4%.
And while a drop in $JUNO’s value, just like any other volatile asset, shouldn’t be a concern in itself. However in this case we believe that this dip is a direct consequence of the recent conflicts within the Juno community and the absence of a clear roadmap for the future of the project.
On the other hand, our conviction on the Akash Network, a project that was on our radar for a long time has only increased. As a decentralized marketplace for computing resources, Akash has a clear product-market fit with a token perfectly positioned to capture value accrued by the network for its holders.
Which is why we are putting forth the proposal of swapping all $JUNO holdings backing $COSC with $AKT for the community to vote on.

# Description:
The careful selection of portfolio assets is critical for an optimal Index token. Which is why Cosmos Core will undergo regular portfolio restructuring to properly benchmark the entire ecosystem. The first portfolio restructuring will seek to gain exposure to decentralized compute providers by adding the Akash Network token, $AKT, to the Cosmos Core’s portfolio. Cosmos Core will use its $JUNO holdings to acquire the $AKT tokens.
Note: At the time of writing, Cosmos Core has approximately 17.34k staked $JUNO.

If passed, Cosmos Core’s staked $JUNO tokens will be unbonded, then swapped to $AKT on Osmosis DEX. Below you can see the list assets in Cosmos Core’s portfolio before and after the proposed change:

 Old Portfolio
* Cosmos Hub - $ATOM
* Osmosis - $OSMO
* Kujira - $KUJI
* Stargaze - $STARS
* Ki Chain - $XKI
* Juno - $JUNO
* Agoric - $BLD

New Portfolio
* Cosmos Hub - $ATOM
* Osmosis - $OSMO
* Kujira - $KUJI
* Stargaze - $STARS
* Ki Chain - $XKI
* Akash - $AKT
* Agoric - $BLD

By voting YES to this proposal you agree to adding $AKT to Cosmos Core’s portfolio by liquidating its $JUNO holdings.
 By voting NO to this proposal you do not agree to adding $AKT to Cosmos Core’s portfolio by liquidating its $JUNO holdings.
 By voting No With Veto you deem this proposal harmful to Cosmos Core.
 By voting abstain you signal your desire to contribute to quorum without a preference toward whether the proposal passes or fails.

detail.title: XKI v2
detail.description:
# XKI v2 Tokenomics

The Ki Foundation team has been working hard these last few months with many products being built and ready to release. To accompany the continuing growth of Klub activity and the launch of new products (like Atlas) and enable the capture of the value generated through these products, it is crucial to establish a sound tokenomics framework that aligns with rational principles. We propose to implement the XKI v2 tokenomics as follows:

a) A fixed total supply of 1.2Billion $XKI,
b) A -25% reduction of the inflation rate every 4 months with a final goal inflation of 1%
 c) The introduction of a usage tax on the revenue of products and businesses built or using the KiChain of 15% to fuel the token burn.

If this proposal is validated by the community, these steps will follow:
- Perform at least the first inflation reduction for the first phase (Juin-October) according to the reduction agenda through a governance proposal.
- Implement the supply bounding in the KiChain client and perform a chain upgrade accordingly.

More details about Klub, Atlas and the new tokenomics can be found in the [AMA](https://us06web.zoom.us/rec/share/BMV3hfkvFskz0uTVu8gnq1PVAhL97NDM1bEUtRfCQhu0w_tKqmm4Ozgamp2jtpj7.s26vcjlue4RZS18T).

This is a signaling proposal to assess the community opinion on the implementation of the new tokenomics. By voting yes to this proposal the community agrees on implementing the new XKI tokenomics according to the aforementioned agenda.

detail.title: Reduce Deposit Time
detail.description:
# Reduce Deposit Time

This proposal aims at reducing the deposit time for governance proposals from 7 days to 2 days. This allows a faster discard of spam proposals which never reach the minimum deposit requirement. The voting period stays unchanged at 3 days.

By voting YES to this proposal the KiChain community agrees on reducing the deposit time for governance proposals to 2 days

detail.title: V5 Upgrade Proposal
detail.description:
# Kichain V5 Upgrade

By voting YES to this proposal the Kichain community agrees on performing the V5 upgrade on the Kichain Mainnet `kichain-2`.

This upgrade brings the following features:
* Cosmos SDK v0.45.12
* IBC v3.3.1
* CosmWasm v0.29.2 

# Upgrade plan

The upgrade is set to occur at height `14340215`, which should be reached on `Thursday March 23rd at 13H00 UTC` based on the current block time of 5.7sec computed over the last 50000 blocks. The block countdown can be found on mintscan [here](https://www.mintscan.io/ki-chain/blocks/14340215). 

This upgrade will use [`v5.0.0`](https://github.com/KiFoundation/ki-tools/releases/tag/5.0.0) of the Kichain client `ki-tools`, a full tutorial on how to apply the upgrade can be found [here](https://github.com/KiFoundation/ki-networks/blob/v0.1/Mainnet/kichain-2/UPGRADE_V5.md).

detail.title: Increase Community Tax
detail.description:
# Increase Community Tax

This proposal aims at reapplying the community tax change voted by the community in proposal 3. The change had to be reverted with a client update due to a misconfigured distribution in the aforementioned proposal which halted the chain.

 By voting YES to this proposal the KiChain community agrees on the following : 

* Increase the community tax from 4% to 10%
* Reduce the base propose reward accordingly to 86%

detail.title: Inflation and Community tax parameter change
detail.description:
# From Ki 1.0 to Ki 2.0

This proposal aims to make the XKI tokenomics evolve into a new era.

 After Cosmon being delivered and soon governed by the community, Atlas soon to come with fully decentralized products, we need to bring the XKI to its new shape and form. This proposal aims to :

* Raise the minimum inflation rate from 2% to 8%
* Reduce the maximum inflation rate from 14% to 12%
* Bring 10% of the inflation directly to the community pool

This new strategy will enable the stability of the network for stakers but also to help fund future incentive programs to be deployed in a few weeks by the community pool.
